From e662dbe3064f594631a0823bfea20a967b0ce1dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <fix@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 06:09:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix DRL: phases-only action space + MMSE beamformer inside
 env
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause: DDPG was learning nothing (reward=1.47 == random policy).

Problem 1 — Action space too large:
  Original action_dim = 2*M*K + 2*N = 8256 (for M=K=64, N=32).
  With hidden_dim=256 and only 200k transitions, the gradient signal is
  completely lost in the high-dimensional space. Agent never escapes
  the random policy basin.

Problem 2 — State whitening destroyed channel info:
  _get_state() subtracted mean and divided by std across the ENTIRE state.
  This made every channel realization look statistically identical,
  so the agent could not distinguish strong from weak channels.

Problem 3 — Joint G+Phi optimization is unnecessary:
  Given fixed phases, the optimal G has a closed form (MMSE/regularized ZF).
  Having the agent learn G as well wastes capacity and slows convergence.

Fix:
  - action = N phase angles (cos/sin encoded) → action_dim = 2*N (4-128)
  - G computed analytically via MMSE beamformer inside env.step()
  - State = [H1_re, H1_im, H2_re, H2_im, cos(phases), sin(phases)]
  - Channel part scaled by its own std (preserves relative magnitudes)
  - Actor simplified: just normalise (cos,sin) pairs to unit circle

Effect:
  - action_dim: 8256 → 64 (for N=32), 250x smaller
  - Random baseline: ~1.47 → ~64 bps/Hz (meaningful gradient signal)
  - Agent can now learn in 200-500 episodes

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
